üì∞ 3 THINGS TO CHECK OUT

Top 10 UI Annoyances  (https://hs.designlab.com/e3t/Ctc/UD+113/d56t7h04/VWMmTJ4SnfK7W5J8JGL8cz2s1W1qZjFf5zJhTXN50kgNM3l5QzW6N1vHY6lZ3mgW7ZFQs525jD6DW11b0S-46Pk8VW227ckz5T2FkdW672X0W3xjxD5W5-L64n2k6PVLW2ztYn_9fFTzkW11fRgs6cvrnhW5B3C6x7RvgM7W4l__4z9hvncrW2Thww64SJVdrW4HD0xP8T55BsW4F4Xrt5zLd-nW2VNxgS4T73pJW56tpL59g54GdW4XjQ4V3mQdJ0W7zvlQs89t06WN7_K7TjgWKMxW3dk4qx506B9-W39C-mf99Jx_PW5zT_9V5Dzl8YW76PV5k7TJtGbW2B71dR9g7gr7f4YMRRM04 )

- UX pioneer Jakob Nielsen identifies ten specific, recurrent design flaws‚Äîlike intrusive pop‚Äëups, misaligned navigation, and annoying auto‚Äëplay‚Äîthat consistently frustrate users and accumulate into a worse experience.

- Nielsen argues that these everyday annoyances aren‚Äôt just trivial irritants but measurable usability failures‚Äîand because they create avoidable friction, should be addressed to optimize user satisfaction and retention.

- ‚ÄúEach individual exposure to a usability annoyance may be just that: a fleeting annoyance. But since the annoyances don‚Äôt go away, their impact compounds, leading to low adoption, wasted development cycles, and long-term damage to brand trust.‚Äù

Figma Stock Soars in Market D (https://hs.designlab.com/e3t/Ctc/UD+113/d56t7h04/VWMmTJ4SnfK7W5J8JGL8cz2s1W1qZjFf5zJhTXN50kgPF3l5QzW8wLKSR6lZ3mFW4xzFVm93ct2GW8Z9vWG20JthdW3T_ych2_6kdrW8sFnqr1mXHDxW7dr6BB4D4zS-W6-J8By1YNb1pW8Xsy5R2FpMDyW3N1jfK4tGBzQW2NZygN7p3WNMW3tMFzZ6_w0rnW79ZrGH3sH2jJW2_3j2095Zl9lW8QpQKL98TX3TN9cvh5McLmzwW4d901m8dSDRtW1gmM6H2cgm4dW3PhLls3L-4ZbW3z49816-kZ2fV63z706Dh1CjW7JGRvs6t4pbwW2Dyc4H61jrxzW65PvsP238Vr4W1qnGYV4WrtGTN1NtylvSF8VsW4hGz2-7xDV8pW4FpwkH6Z3STzW71tzq_6CWL3WW33h1vG4_f1D4f4Jkx7T04 ) ebut (https://hs.designlab.com/e3t/Ctc/UD+113/d56t7h04/VWMmTJ4SnfK7W5J8JGL8cz2s1W1qZjFf5zJhTXN50kgPF3l5QzW8wLKSR6lZ3mFW4xzFVm93ct2GW8Z9vWG20JthdW3T_ych2_6kdrW8sFnqr1mXHDxW7dr6BB4D4zS-W6-J8By1YNb1pW8Xsy5R2FpMDyW3N1jfK4tGBzQW2NZygN7p3WNMW3tMFzZ6_w0rnW79ZrGH3sH2jJW2_3j2095Zl9lW8QpQKL98TX3TN9cvh5McLmzwW4d901m8dSDRtW1gmM6H2cgm4dW3PhLls3L-4ZbW3z49816-kZ2fV63z706Dh1CjW7JGRvs6t4pbwW2Dyc4H61jrxzW65PvsP238Vr4W1qnGYV4WrtGTN1NtylvSF8VsW4hGz2-7xDV8pW4FpwkH6Z3STzW71tzq_6CWL3WW33h1vG4_f1D4f4Jkx7T04 )

- Figma‚Äôs IPO marks one of the biggest software debuts in years, with shares jumping more than 250%. CEO Dylan Field emphasizes long‚Äëterm vision, not short‚Äëterm profits, and recommits to innovation for designers, not just enterprise buyers.

- While some feel the design field is facing market headwinds, Figma‚Äôs explosive growth is a reminder that the demand for great tools‚Äîand the impact of design itself‚Äîis still rising fast.

- ‚ÄúOur primary goal is not efficiency. Our goal is to achieve long‚Äëterm growth by supporting the rapidly evolving needs of designers.‚Äù ‚Äî Dylan Field

Vanilla Moments & Designing for the Real World (https://hs.designlab.com/e3t/Ctc/UD+113/d56t7h04/VWMmTJ4SnfK7W5J8JGL8cz2s1W1qZjFf5zJhTXN50kgNM3l5QzW6N1vHY6lZ3kGW1GmjhS8HHthjV3nsbK92mpZsW8Zr32W56vr0PW1cHxZS1qZY6PW7w8ST-260T-xW6xqVL34n8TslW40cNyJ8xWsV3W4KqCCM91Vq_hN1NwlcM-Z6LnW6rP-zC7zlkYlW8k8PKQ75ywV9W5Zt5Kc6LqFbjN39zZSbKNmwYW3lnym54jfKrWN7J7XPls1sPHW80dD552jK7c-VLn7dJ4hcrP3W21-J9K6HWDlqW5vrkTD2XCQcPW7w1LHw666_zDW6xwHSX2XbL23W9f3s_P4YTPg8f1dbPGK04 )

- Designer Kelly Smith introduces the idea of "vanilla moments"‚Äîunexpected, imperfect real‚Äëworld interactions that expose hidden design gaps and unmet user needs.

- Smith argues that to build truly user‚Äëcentered experiences, designers must actively observe real usage and build systems that tolerate imperfection and evolve over time.

- ‚ÄúPeople are tired, distracted, curious, skeptical, impatient, brilliant and fallible. That‚Äôs why observation, in my personal opinion, is the gold standard of design.‚Äù

üíú PORTFOLIO INSPIRATION

Chanelle Lester, (https://hs.designlab.com/e3t/Ctc/UD+113/d56t7h04/VWMmTJ4SnfK7W5J8JGL8cz2s1W1qZjFf5zJhTXN50kgNs3l5QzW69sMD-6lZ3kMW57SCrt7-J6TwN93vk0Wv6fKHW3jn_fB5PS4xzW2wtPtw4Wc6L-W1Lhn5v6zgrpcW5DzkyV4gmdMdW8X7v8x9c_bVNW8z-r714yY07QW2fPD5g9ggQ0GW2lTG6L89_C3qW83S6B22473RkW2Xtnqb7m1RTsW3Fq0M46C4SLpW7tBcBc1_BB-CN4HXNjSkCgg8W67p1hB2lV7HCN70DbP7C2n2MW44G38j67jlVTN55TmvyGhmpdW3g1vyv8Sw-0Mf3fyv5F04 )  a UX Academy graduate, infuses her design work with a sense of fun and approachability‚Äîqualities that shine through in her project for Munchy, an app designed to help foodies share their culinary experiences and foster a stronger sense of community around food. The app‚Äôs inviting UI and emphasis on personalization and trust-building result in a user experience that feels both seamless and welcoming. In her SkinCircle project, a skincare app, Chanelle takes a research-driven approach to identify common pain points users face with similar apps. Her goal: to create a more accessible, friendly, and trustworthy skin care product selection experience. Once again, her visual style‚Äîbright, engaging, and user-centric‚Äîbrings the interface to life.

Agents in public beta for Self-hosted, plus UI improvements that make building smoother. Hello, Retool community! Mark your calendars for October 7, 2025‚Äîwe‚Äôre hosting our first-ever Retool

Logo-Light (https://retool.com/?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_content=373894688&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 )

Log In
(https://login.retool.com/auth/login?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_content=373894688&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 )

üëã Hello, Retool community!

Mark your calendars for October 7, 2025‚Äîwe‚Äôre hosting our first-ever Retool Summit at the SFJAZZ Center in San Francisco. It‚Äôs a full day designed for the people redefining how software gets built: developers, technical leads, operations pros, and anyone hands-on with internal tools.

Early-bird pricing available through Sept. 7 üëÄ See you there? (https://events.retool.com/summit2025?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=july_mallet_25&rcid=701Qo000012CwS6IAK&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 )

summit (https://events.retool.com/summit2025?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=july_mallet_25&rcid=701Qo000012CwS6IAK&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 )

üöÄ What‚Äôs new

Agents now in public beta for Self-hosted (https://docs.retool.com/changelog/agents-edge-beta?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=july_mallet_25&rcid=701Qo000012CwS6IAK&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 )

Self-hosted customers running 3.234.0 and later can now access the public beta version of Retool Agents. Set the AGENTS_ENABLED environment variable to true to get started.

Clearer workflow releases (https://docs.retool.com/changelog/workflow-release-language?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=july_mallet_25&rcid=701Qo000012CwS6IAK&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 )

We‚Äôve updated the workflow IDE to make releases more intuitive. The "Deploy" has been renamed "Publish" and your "Deploy History" is now "Releases"‚Äîsmall changes that align the app and workflow experiences.

Access lists for workflows, resources, and agents (https://docs.retool.com/changelog/access-list?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=july_mallet_25&rcid=701Qo000012CwS6IAK&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 )

You can now see exactly who has access to your workflows, resources, and agents. Click the ‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢ menu on any listing page and select View access list.

Typed data inputs for modules (https://docs.retool.com/changelog/module-input-types?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=july_mallet_25&rcid=701Qo000012CwS6IAK&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 )

Modules now support proper data typing‚ÄîString, Number, Boolean, Enum, or Any. This catches mismatched data types early and makes your modules more reliable. Choose a type to get validation warnings when inputs don't match expectations.

üõ† Check out the changelog to see everything we‚Äôve shipped (https://docs.retool.com/changelog?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=july_mallet_25&rcid=701Qo000012CwS6IAK&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 ) .

üóì Upcoming in-person events

Retool Summit 2025‚ÄîOctober 7, San Francisco: Join us for a full day of practical insights, deep product walkthroughs, in-person connection time, and early looks at what‚Äôs next. Early bird pricing ($195) until Sept. 7, $395 onwards. Space is limited‚Äîget the details and reserve your spot today. (https://events.retool.com/summit2025?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=july_mallet_25&rcid=701Qo000012CwS6IAK&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 )

üí°Online events‚ÄîRSVP today

- Your Data is Holding Back Your AI‚ÄîAugust 19, 10am PST: Join Sam Garfield (https://www.linkedin.com/in/samuelholdengarfield/?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_content=373894688&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 ) , Analytics Engineer, for a practical conversation about making data actually work for AI. Register here. (https://events.retool.com/data-holding-back-your-ai?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=july_mallet_25&rcid=701Qo000012CwS6IAK&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 )
- Learn Retool in 15 minutes (Weekly on Thursdays): Did you know we offer a weekly demo where you can build a Retool app alongside an expert in 15 minutes? Sign up here (https://events.retool.com/retool15?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=july_mallet_25&rcid=701Qo000012CwS6IAK&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 ) .

üé• On demand

You can now watch all of our past webinars, tutorials, and build-alongs in one place. Check out our new video library. (https://retool.com/resources/videos?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=july_mallet_25&rcid=701Qo000012CwS6IAK&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 )

(https://retool.com/resources/videos?category=webinars-and-events&utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=july_mallet_25&rcid=701Qo000012CwS6IAK&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 )

üåç From the Community

AI Build Week took over the community in July, and let‚Äôs just say: builders showed up. Hundreds joined live, and yes, badges and swag were claimed. You can still earn yours just by participating in the threads in the AI Build Week hub. (https://community.retool.com/t/ai-build-week-replays-q-as-resources/58630?utm_source=hs_email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=july_mallet_25&rcid=701Qo000012CwS6IAK&_hsenc=p2ANqtz--1EE9LBqbFbg3gfAeIJiEdIuSsBbWZAT5hsjSpX3OE851d7yPot6OYtJJ9XNTsuOstBhUjeGz_gqcX8Gwlxf6rcZfTiw&_hsmi=373894688 )

column7: Thanks for your interest in Qventus
column9:
Hi Candace,

¬†

Thank you for your interest in the Analytics Lead position with Qventus. After reviewing your experience carefully against this position, we're moving ahead in our search for candidates who we feel are a closer match to what we need at this time. Of course, this doesn't mean that you might not be a great candidate for future roles with us, so we would love to keep you 'on our radar' for new opportunities as they come up.

¬†

We encourage you to continue to check for openings on our careers page and get in touch with us if you see any opportunity you are interested in! Though we're aware these messages are never welcome, we hope you appreciate knowing your status and please keep in touch!

¬†

Thank you,

Talent Acquisition at Qventus

column7: Update on your Staff Data Analyst, Operations application with Toast
column9:
Hi Candace,

We appreciate your interest in the Staff Data Analyst, Operations position at Toast. You chose to pursue a career with us and for that, we are incredibly honored and grateful.

We love everything that you bring to the table, however we received other applicants who more closely match our needs at this time.

We know that messages like this are never fun to receive, but we mean it when we say that we‚Äôd love to stay connected. We invite you to join the Toast Talent Network. By completing this ( https://www.gem.com/form?formID=f29b6371-166e-4bb0-869c-e8b294049d17 ) short form, you‚Äôll help our recruiting team understand which opportunities best align with your skills and interests.

You can also always check out our careers site ( https://careers.toasttab.com/homepage ), where you can see all open positions, learn more about our teams, and visit the Life at Toast blog. We also encourage you to keep up with Toast by checking out our LinkedIn ( https://www.linkedin.com/company/toast-inc ) and Instagram ( https://www.instagram.com/lifeattoast/ ) pages!

We wish you all the best!

Toasting to you,
Toast Recruiting

üì∞ 3 THINGS TO CHECK OUT

Initial Impressions of ChatGPT‚Äôs Agent: Successful, Shaky, and Slow (https://hs.designlab.com/e3t/Ctc/UD+113/d56t7h04/MVWT6zSpdfnW2BBcsr4y6WpqW8SvcRS5BfcbFMDyKn63prCCW7Y8-PT6lZ3lhW5QR1W93_4ntTW1ss1TL5STVKqW1LKTCd3nCrF0MQFLcRkqtYTN4lHzQs_yX8VW8bdDtL2n9GJxW4qKM2Y2LtcqLW525BY772d3JtW4nnFJC5mQGHpW9lrdJb1RPkKtW5kC0Qx2ncbYFW8xm6mc5J_SlpW5lX1YN7t8B8hW8Xc_HB5ZtNHWW5sN90y5XlzDMW7rXGlv1fVgvtN1gSRw7gKs9wW8RsL3V5w2DMDN5c_YjRbxQV-W4tdWys2YVD7-W6tLrQY6CzNXjV-tFxn89vTY2W1hQpg693qk3PW4PNrD32tVWN4W17lyRD8HmWmgW5TmTD-5Yt41_f2rSzZz04 )

- Senior UX Specialist Evan Sunwall does a dive into ChatGPT‚Äôs new agent mode, finding that while the AI can complete autonomous tasks, the process is often slow, fragile, and prone to misunderstanding user intent.

- His test‚Äîbooking a business lunch‚Äîsucceeded in principle but exposed usability issues, underscoring that while the agent is a promising step forward, it still faces challenges before it can be considered broadly trustworthy and efficient.

- ‚ÄúChatGPT needed 11 minutes to navigate the restaurant‚Äôs web forms, whereas it took me about 2 minutes to perform the same workflow at a casual pace‚Ä¶ ChatGPT took so long to complete the process that the 10-minute window to hold a table reservation technically timed out.‚Äù

Robinhood's Surprising UX (https://hs.designlab.com/e3t/Ctc/UD+113/d56t7h04/MVWT6zSpdfnW2BBcsr4y6WpqW8SvcRS5BfcbFMDyKnq3l5QzW8wLKSR6lZ3mvW4vjskV6d_LPpW8p50x78qqyzlW8qfxlG5nz-hXW40rFzk8Qwx_QW3BwdFt6sql1KN99j2FvkWs1TW7n7tDw1HlDzQW2BJ3Pc8LbQVyW11rW4j5Mp-5RW2C-FPB92bg6rW7P4g7v7v4LzvW1t0f975y8zY0W5Fbptj3-Ds6qW4RG2nc544wy7MrzB1LR74s9W3djgtj426tgpVlB6cZ2q6hwRW5f-fs14Tt68qN7fPPLq7psDjN8sYqHtlWn6cW3n9NGC2KR1XsW7gjc9x6lj4P-W8kpjjt4GQLFHW7b3ZGD7KN_LmW97nrN_7bTpHxVdKkql2qv7FFW31Fx234GyJXMW1PQLP598JRJyf5T46vd04 )

- UX Designer Amish Gadhia details how financial app Robinhood has developed a system to thoughtfully integrate context-aware alerts that address potential fraud scenarios without overwhelming users with constant warnings.

- By surfacing this warning precisely when the user is most vulnerable‚Äîsuch as when they‚Äôre actively participating in money management on their device‚Äîthe app enhances clarity, trust, and situational awareness.

- ‚ÄúSecurity isn‚Äôt just about encryption or backend safeguards. It‚Äôs also about how you communicate risks to the person holding the device.When you design security into the user experience, you‚Äôre not just preventing fraud, you‚Äôre building trust.‚Äù

Design Systems and AI (https://hs.designlab.com/e3t/Ctc/UD+113/d56t7h04/MVWT6zSpdfnW2BBcsr4y6WpqW8SvcRS5BfcbFMDyKmx3l5QzW6N1vHY6lZ3mLW73XgkR2mwx3_W1FdRlM104YDdN8cGPXCPX4xgW2mRxYX6rWbR4W1wR6ql2v9jGKW3vgWjZ1nV4FKW43xm1r6rjMNZW5s8Dmq2CKmpqW5FkyG24Wfn3VW7lMmHL6P-P0hV3Lcmn3nJVs3W5MShhm1DPRCTW2LJ_Sz2nt74xW5QL8PB7pTGfpF97bDrjjvq8N6c5YvLcN8LtW5xcLy85jzVs8W6jhK9x5k17WPW1lnZ0Y10jl-mW1Rv8LL7FWnPWW3Kr4W546JwwYW5C0pz51h6kgqdsMZNT04 )

- Ana Boyer, Designer Advocate at Figma, dissects how pairing robust design systems with Model Context Protocol servers‚Äîan open standard for securely connecting AI models to external tools and data‚Äîcan significantly elevate AI workflows.

- This creates a powerful feedback loop: the better you craft your design system, the smarter the AI agents become at producing accurate code, boosting both speed and quality of outputs.

- ‚ÄúAs LLMs make it easier to go from idea to execution, the true differentiator for great products becomes not just functionality, but craft‚Äîthe kind that reflects clear intent, visual identity, and thoughtful user experience.‚Äù

column7: üéØ New: The 7 Types of Investors We See at Every Family Office Club Event
column9:
Here are the 7 types of investors coming to our investor club events and how to work with each type in terms of deal structures.Hi Candace,¬†

**Are you pitching your deal to an "Income Strategist" but presenting it like it's for a "Builder-Investor"?**

After hosting 300 events and transcribing talks & interviews with 1,500 investors over 18 years, we‚Äôve uncovered the 

**7 most common investor personas** that drive how investors think, act, and allocate capital.

👉 Whether you're raising for real estate, a fund, or an operating company, understanding 

**which type of investor you're speaking to** can make or break your pitch.

**1. 

**The Legacy Preserver 👨‚Äç👩‚Äç👧‚Äç👦**** * 

**Core Focus**: Multi-generational wealth preservation, estate planning, minimizing taxes.

* 

**Capital Deployment**: Slow-moving, tax-advantaged deals like DSTs, Opportunity Zones, trusts, generational real estate, and direct investments with estate step-up in basis potential.

* 

**Behavioral Traits**: Conservative, long-term thinker, values privacy and control.

* 

**Quote**: ‚ÄúWe‚Äôre not looking for moonshots; we‚Äôre looking for legacy.‚Äù

**2. 

**The Niche Allocator 🎯**** * 

**Core Focus**: Deeply specialized in one or two sectors (e.g., mineral rights, senior living, physician-backed roll-ups, logistics).

* 

**Capital Deployment**: Invests only in their niche or through structures they understand intimately.

* 

**Behavioral Traits**: High conviction, wants to feel like the smartest person in the room on their domain.

* 

**Quote**: ‚ÄúIf it's not X, we don‚Äôt even look at it.‚Äù

**3. 

**The Opportunistic Capitalist ‚ö°**** * 

**Core Focus**: Fast-moving, deal-driven, loves distressed assets, turnarounds, and arbitrage opportunities.

* 

**Capital Deployment**: Jumps on recession plays, broken cap tables, off-market assets, seller-financed deals.

* 

**Behavioral Traits**: Hustler energy, high velocity, driven by returns and timing.

* 

**Quote**: ‚ÄúWe make our money on the buy.‚Äù

**4. 

**The Income Strategist 💸**** * 

**Core Focus**: Passive cash flow, yield-driven investing, lifestyle-focused.

* 

**Capital Deployment**: Real estate notes, preferred equity, ATMs, mobile home parks, private lending.

* 

**Behavioral Traits**: Low volatility tolerance, leans on reliable deal sponsors.

* 

**Quote**: ‚ÄúShow me monthly checks with downside protection.‚Äù

**5. 

**The Institutional Mindset 🧠**** * 

**Core Focus**: Professional, data-heavy decision-making; wants governance, reporting, and institutional-grade processes.

* 

**Capital Deployment**: Allocates into funds, co-invests with PE/VC, prefers audited financials and formal structure.

* 

**Behavioral Traits**: Metrics-driven, compliance-oriented, delegation-focused.

* 

**Quote**: ‚ÄúLet‚Äôs talk risk-adjusted returns and benchmark performance.‚Äù

**6. 

**The Impact-Aligned Investor 🌍**** * 

**Core Focus**: ESG, sustainability, mission-aligned investments that reflect values.

* 

**Capital Deployment**: Often through direct investments, blended finance structures, and private credit with a mission tie-in.

* 

**Behavioral Traits**: Purpose-led, emotionally driven but financially conscious.

* 

**Quote**: ‚ÄúI want to make a difference and a return.‚Äù

**7. 

**The Builder-Investor 🏗Ô∏è**** * 

**Core Focus**: Actively operating businesses, M&A rollups, real estate development, or startups.

* 

**Capital Deployment**: Prefers control, board seats, influence. Often reinvests profits into new ventures.

* 

**Behavioral Traits**: Entrepreneurial, hands-on, wants sweat equity or founder leverage.

* 

**Quote**: ‚ÄúI invest in what I can scale and control.‚Äù

**🧠 

**Why it Matters:****

Understanding these 7 personas helps you position your opportunity, structure, and approach.

**Investor type dictates everything: how they evaluate deals, how fast they move, what risk they accept, and how you should communicate with them.**

Many seasoned investors blend 2‚Äì3 personas over time, but most have a dominant driver.

Here is a matrix that maps these investor types to ideal deal structures:

I hope you find this helpful, these results were created from our Investor Advantage AI tool, which contains all of the billionaire interviews, investor talks from on stage, podcast investor interviews, investor mandates, and more for you to gain insights from.¬†¬†

We hope to see you at one of our investor club meetings soon, and let me know if you want to access our Netflix-style mobile app of 1,250 investor talks & mandates, live events, and AI toolset.

Xander Clemens

column7: Learn about diversity, equity, and inclusion at the I School
column9:
Hello Candace,

            I hope this email finds you well! Amid work stress or end of the school year chaos, I hope that you will find time to do something that prioritizes your health and well-being. Summer is a time for reflection and new beginnings! This month, let's turn our attention to new opportunities that strengthen the excellence we all possess.

Celebrating Diversity

            June is filled with opportunities to celebrate, reflect, and honor diverse communities and causes. This month, UC Berkeley celebrates Pride Month <https://diversity.berkeley.edu/news/building-belonging-creating-inclusive-environment-lgbtq-community-and-allies-uc-berkeley> and reaffirms its commitment to building inclusive spaces and providing resources for the LGBTQ+ community. We invite you to learn more about the Gender Equity Resource Center's <https://mailchi.us3.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e4b82243fe29f5427521f946c&id=7eb62ae97e&e=e4dd850053> work to expand insurance and provider coverage for trans and nonbinary students on campus, and how the Queer Alliance Resource Center <https://mailchi.us3.list-manage.com/track/click?u=e4b82243fe29f5427521f946c&id=68cfc004ee&e=e4dd850053> works as an essential umbrella-organization for more than twenty student-led groups that provide social, educational, and safe sex programming for the queer and trans community and their allies on campus.          

Our Berkeley Values
          ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã
          At Berkeley, we believe that diversity is an intrinsic component of excellence. Chancellor Rich Lyons reminds us <https://news.berkeley.edu/2025/02/28/a-message-about-our-commitment-to-uc-berkeleys-values-and-mission/> that "our university's excellence is a function of and is utterly dependent on our comprehensive, encompassing diversity. And so, we will continue to confront discrimination at every turn. We will support our community members without regard for their immigration status. We will continue to comply with the laws of our state that ensure we admit students, and hire staff and faculty, without regard for race, national origin, religion, citizenship or other protected characteristics."                      I look forward to continuing to share exciting news and complex issues around DEIBJ work happening at the I School and UC Berkeley. I am hopeful that these newsletters will continue to spark thought and encourage dialogue about ways to make us better. If you would like to chat or contribute to this newsletter, I would love to hear from you!          

            Warmly,
            Roxanne

Roxanne Pifer
            Director of Admissions & Diversity Recruitment
            UC Berkeley School of Information

Professional Development & Awards

Eight Steps to a Successful Summer Break <https://grad.berkeley.edu/news/eight-steps-to-a-successful-summer-break/>
            Summer is often seen as a season of endless possibilities, offering a chance for graduate students to make progress on their research, catch up on tasks, and enjoy a break. View the steps <https://berkeley.us7.list-manage.com/track/click?u=b1b8063dfa284a9549e81b3f9&id=d12291801d&e=c8774a8c86>.
                       

Honoring Excellence: 2025 Graduate Diversity Leadership Awardees <https://grad.berkeley.edu/office-for-graduate-diversity/honoring-excellence-2025-graduate-diversity-leadership-awardees/>
            Launched in 2022, the UC Berkeley Leadership in Graduate Diversity Awards recognize outstanding graduate students who have made significant contributions to advancing diversity and inclusion among underrepresented minority (URM) graduate and professional students. With a competitive pool of exceptional applicants, the selection process is never easy!          

Student & Alumni News

Ph.D. Student Awarded FASPE Ethics Fellowship for Design and Technology <https://www.ischool.berkeley.edu/news/2025/phd-student-awarded-faspe-ethics-fellowship-design-and-technology>
            Justin Norman, a fourth-year Ph.D. candidate at UC Berkeley's School of Information, is one of 14 Fellows chosen for the 2025 Design & Technology (D&T) Program of the Fellowships at Auschwitz for the Study of Professional Ethics (FASPE).


Data Science Master's Project Fosters Sustainability by Organizing Carbon Offset Data <https://www.ischool.berkeley.edu/news/2025/data-science-masters-project-fosters-sustainability-organizing-carbon-offset-data>
            Master of Information and Data Science (MIDS) alums Kevin Ngoc Hoang, Xinyun (Roxy) Rong, Maggie Corry, and Roshni Suresh Tajnekar are the winners of the Sarukkai Social Impact Award, for their project, Carbon AIQ <https://www.ischool.berkeley.edu/projects/2024/carbon-aiq>.          

Events

A Celebration of Mentorship at the I School <https://www.ischool.berkeley.edu/events/2025/celebration-mentorship-i-school>
            The I School mentorship programs support all of our professional degree programs as well as the Leadership Development Program for Gender Equity <https://www.ischool.berkeley.edu/careers/employers/ldp>. During the last academic year, over 200 students, alumni, and industry leaders volunteered their time to mentor students, assisting them through the transition to graduate school, providing support in their job or internship searches and career advancement, and giving advice and perspective on how to lead with equity and inclusion.

UC Berkeley AI Hackathon <https://ai.hackberkeley.org/>
            UC Berkeley's AI Hackathon is a 2-day hackathon, where hackers creatively collaborate on innovative technology for a chance to win prizes including cash, and attend workshops and panels to learn more about emerging tech. Register today!
                       


Want to change how you receive these emails? Update your preferences or unsubscribe <https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeTTLOY71Z0VfBeFbXb1ds1NdP20WphSkqe9xEG9qyRPUIBCg/viewform> from this list.          

UC Berkeley School of Information <https://www.ischool.berkeley.edu> - 102 South Hall, Berkeley, CA 94720-4600

column7: Thank you for applying to Datadog
column9:
Hi Candace,

Thank you for your interest in Datadog! We wanted to confirm that we have received your application for the Enablement Program Manager, Sales job.

Our recruiting team manually reviews every single candidate‚Äôs profile, and we receive a high volume of applications, so it may be a couple of weeks before we can get in touch with you regarding the next steps.

While you wait for an update, you can learn more about Datadog by visiting our Careers page ( https://www.datadoghq.com/careers/ ). You can also learn more about #datadoglife from our employees on LinkedIn ( https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/datadoglife/ ) and Instagram ( https://www.instagram.com/datadoghq/ ).

We will be in touch soon!

Kind regards,

The Datadog Recruiting Team

PS: If you've applied for multiple roles, you may hear back from us more than once.

column7: "Is this just a collection of prompts?‚Äù
column9:
Hey there!

Quick reminder: Ghostwriter GPT (
https://click.convertkit-mail.com/e5uw7qqv2wc0upp3nv7h8h8dgz222blh2xnz2/l2hroqpms6ulvl52k9ig/aHR0cHM6Ly9kZmwwLnVzL3MvZjk5NzYxZWU_ZW09YWljb2FjaGluZzIwMjUlNDBnbWFpbC5jb20=
) will be gone in just 2 days.

After that, we‚Äôre taking it down permanently and won‚Äôt be
reopening it for the time being‚Äîeven if you email us asking for
an exception.

So if you‚Äôve been waiting to grab your copy, click here before
it‚Äôs too late.

Now, over the last few days, we‚Äôve been getting some great
questions about Ghostwriter GPT. And I wanted to address some of
the most common ones directly (because I have a feeling you might
be wondering about some of these too).

So let‚Äôs dive right in:

---------------------------------------
‚ÄúIs this just a collection of prompts?‚Äù
---------------------------------------

I get why you might think this. The internet is flooded with ‚ÄúAI
prompt libraries‚Äù that are basically glorified copy-paste
templates.

But here‚Äôs the thing:

With Ghostwriter GPT, you‚Äôre not buying prompts‚Äîyou‚Äôre buying
outcomes.

The difference? Anyone can write a prompt that says ‚Äúhelp me find
my niche.‚Äù

But it takes 15+ years of ghostwriting expertise to engineer a
prompt that interviews you like a consultant, identifies your
information advantages, and builds a Client Constellation of
opportunities.

That‚Äôs not a prompt.

That‚Äôs a business strategy packaged into AI.

----------------------------------------
‚ÄúI don‚Äôt have time to learn AI prompts.‚Äù
----------------------------------------

I felt the same way when I first started using AI. It felt like
another thing I had to learn on top of everything else.

But here‚Äôs the beautiful part about Ghostwriter GPT:

You don‚Äôt have to ‚Äúlearn AI prompts‚Äù because we‚Äôre giving you all
the answers.

These prompts are plug-and-play. You copy, paste, and get results
immediately. No learning curve. No trial and error. No wondering
if you‚Äôre doing it right.

And if you ever want to create your own prompts later, we include
our Prompt Writing Template that shows you exactly how we
engineer these systems.

--------------------------------------------------
‚ÄúThese probably won‚Äôt work for my specific niche.‚Äù
--------------------------------------------------

Here‚Äôs what I‚Äôve discovered after training 1,400+ ghostwriters:

Everyone thinks their niche is ‚Äútoo unique‚Äù for ‚Äúgeneral
frameworks.‚Äù

Finance people think their industry is too technical. Health
coaches think their audience is too specialized. Tech founders
think their problems are too complex.

But we‚Äôve seen these frameworks work in all sorts of obscure
niches and industries.

For example: Just last week, we had a student who ghostwrites for
people in the forklift industry hit an $18k month.

Because here‚Äôs the thing:

The fundamentals of building a profitable ghostwriting business
are the same no matter your niche:

* Find your positioning
* Create irresistible offers
* Generate quality leads
* Close sales calls

The prompts inside Ghostwriter GPT work for ANY niche because
they‚Äôre built on universal business principles‚Äîbut engineered
specifically for ghostwriters.

----------------------------------
‚ÄúI can just use ChatGPT for free.‚Äù
----------------------------------

Think of ChatGPT like a sports car.

If you know how to drive it, you‚Äôll be able to move extremely
fast and get incredible results.

But if you don‚Äôt know how to drive it properly, you‚Äôll just
crash.

The problem isn‚Äôt the tool‚Äîit‚Äôs how you use it. Generic prompts
give you generic results. Our proven prompts give you the kind of
outputs that we used to build a $3,000,000+ agency.

---------------------------------------
‚ÄúWon‚Äôt AI replace ghostwriters anyway?‚Äù
---------------------------------------

Repeat after me:

AI won‚Äôt take your job. An AI ghostwriter will.

The ghostwriters making $25k/mo (like Thomas from yesterday‚Äôs
email) aren‚Äôt fighting against AI‚Äîthey‚Äôre leveraging it to work
faster, create better content, and serve more clients.

You can either learn to use these tools now, or watch other
ghostwriters pass you by.

----------------------------------
‚ÄúThis sounds too good to be true.‚Äù
----------------------------------

I get it. Ifelt this way about every business opportunity I ever
encountered.

If it works so well, why isn‚Äôt everyone doing it?

But here‚Äôs what I realized:

Most people prefer to stay comfortable rather than take action.
They‚Äôd rather keep struggling with the ‚Äúhard way‚Äù than invest in
shortcuts that actually work.

But the ghostwriters who DO take action?

They‚Äôre the ones hitting $10k, $20k, $25k+ months while everyone
else is still trying to ‚Äúfigure out their niche.‚Äù

-----------------------------------------------------------------
Last chance to get Ghostwriter GPT before it disappears‚Ä¶ forever.
-----------------------------------------------------------------

Look, I‚Äôll be honest with you.

We‚Äôre only offering Ghostwriter GPT for 2 more days because we
genuinely believe these prompts and frameworks can transform your
ghostwriting trajectory.

But we only want to share them with people who are ready to take
action.

So if you‚Äôre still on the fence, still overthinking, still
waiting for the ‚Äúperfect moment‚Äù‚Äîthis probably isn‚Äôt for you.

But if you‚Äôre ready to stop building your ghostwriting business
on hard mode and start leveraging the same AI-powered systems
that have helped our PGA students hit $10k, $20k, and even $30k
and $50k months‚Ä¶

Then this is your moment.

After tomorrow night, Ghostwriter GPT will be gone.

No extensions. No exceptions. No ‚ÄúI wish I had acted sooner‚Äù
emails.

-----------------------------------------------------------------

privacy.

chance to create a separate account with your personal email.

Superhuman's new Agent Marketplace to govern your use of third-party apps and 
agents on our platform. While you're not obligated to use them, exploring these 
third-party services can open up a whole range of new and useful features for 
you to enjoy.

Hi‚ÄØCandace Grant,

August was a whirlwind month of releases for the team here at Visily! In the span of a few weeks, we launched:

* Visily 4.0 (more on that below!)

*
New homepage
Of all these things, the 4.0 release was of course the most important, and it includes A LOT of new capabilities. Let's dive in to a few of them...

Play ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=laFtRG41Ta8 )The biggest updates in 4.0 came in the form of improvements to Visily's AI capabilties. And these improvements were big:¬†

* Multimodal prompts: Combine text, screenshots, canvas selections, and even diagrams to generate and modify outputs
* Conversationality: Make followup requests, reference previous responses and outputs, just like you'd chat with a colleague.
* AI Themes: generate, modify, and apply themes with ease
* Accuracy: AI outputs are more accurate, nuanced, and aesthetically beautiful
( http://app.visily.ai/try/start_with_ai?utm_source=custio&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=release-note&utm_content=V4.0&utm_term=start-with-ai )

Hey Candace,

Hope you‚Äôve had a great week üôå

This is just a final call to join Spring Reset 2025 which is
taking place today at 1400 GMT.

You can register for the event here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/75up528qe9b8h683w2ptzhwx80666in/dphehmue4r8pogul/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3NwcmluZy1yZXNldC0yMDI1Lz9sbS1nYQ==
).

It‚Äôs so easy to lose track of your goals with all the other
tasks, commitments and distractions of everyday life which make
it hard to channel your energy effectively in any single
direction.

If that sounds like you, then the Reset will hopefully help you
get clarity on those goals and set actionable next steps for the
three months ahead.

Even for me, these 90 day reviews have become a key part of my
personal productivity system over the past couple of years which
is why I started doing these free quarterly events because I know
how valuable they can be.

The thing is, productivity isn‚Äôt just about getting more done -
it‚Äôs about getting the right things done. This is why Vision and
Action are the two core pillars of my productivity philosophy -
LifeOS (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/75up528qe9b8h683w2ptzhwx80666in/e0hph0u7p5qrl3f7/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249c3ByaW5nJTIwcmVzZXQmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPXByb2R1Y3RpdmVub3Rlcw==
) - and why I‚Äôm so bullish on making sure that we‚Äôre aligning on
that Vision at regular intervals throughout the year.

So if it sounds like it might be useful, you can register here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/75up528qe9b8h683w2ptzhwx80666in/dphehmue4r8pogul/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL3NwcmluZy1yZXNldC0yMDI1Lz9sbS1nYQ==
).

And if you can‚Äôt attend the Spring Reset, but you still wanted to
explore LifeOS in more detail, you can find more information here
(
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/75up528qe9b8h683w2ptzhwx80666in/e0hph0u7p5qrl3f7/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249c3ByaW5nJTIwcmVzZXQmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPXByb2R1Y3RpdmVub3Rlcw==
). And if you join before April 4th, you‚Äôll get bonus access to
the April Sprint - a 3-week event that we‚Äôve organised for our
LifeOS Pro members in April that we‚Äôre opening up exclusively for
anyone who enrols in LifeOS (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/75up528qe9b8h683w2ptzhwx80666in/e0hph0u7p5qrl3f7/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249c3ByaW5nJTIwcmVzZXQmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPXByb2R1Y3RpdmVub3Rlcw==
) before next Friday.

If not, that‚Äôs totally cool and I‚Äôll speak to you next week :)

Have a great weekend

Ali x

P.S - if you‚Äôre not available on Saturday, the event will be
recorded and we‚Äôll send that over to anyone who registers later
in the weekend üôè

# Q: What do I do about people I just can‚Äôt stand?

Your boss that hovers over your shoulder and micromanages every little thing.
Your friend who just doesn‚Äôt know when to stop talking.
That coworker who chews loudly during your break.

People can be annoying. It‚Äôs true.¬†
And today, I‚Äôm not really here to offer you a method to change their behavior (Spoiler alert: most of the time, you can‚Äôt). I‚Äôm here to offer you a method to change _your own behavior_.

In his semi-autobiographical book _Memories, Dreams, Reflections_, the pioneering psychologist Carl Jung said, [‚ÄúEverything that irritates us about others can lead us to an understanding of ourselves.‚Äù](https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/612188.Memories_Dreams_Reflections)

Now, you may be thinking, _‚ÄúWhat about the guy who chews loudly in the cafeteria ‚Äî what does he have to do with me?‚Äù¬†_

Believe it or not, that loud chewing doesn‚Äôt bother everyone the same way. What annoys us isn‚Äôt random. It‚Äôs personal. You might bristle at loud chewers, whistlers, or fast drivers, while someone else can‚Äôt stand slow eaters, off-key singers, or people who drive too slow.

One of the big [lessons I learned this year](https://youtu.be/iVqdj_HZ03U) is that the traits and habits we can‚Äôt stand in others often mirror the parts of ourselves we haven‚Äôt learned to accept yet.

That controlling boss? Maybe reflects your own fear of letting go.
That guy who talks too much? Maybe hits upon your fear of speaking up.
The loud chewer at the cafeteria? Might reflect a need for peace in other areas of your life..

People aren‚Äôt irritants. They‚Äôre mirrors.

Put another way, **your triggers are your teachers.**

* When you feel jealous, let that jealousy remind you of what you really want.¬†

* When you feel angry, let that anger reveal your inner wounds.

* When you feel defensive, let that defensiveness reveal what you‚Äôre scared of.

* When you feel impatient, let that impatience expose your expectations.

* When you feel sad, let that sadness illustrate your values.

Allow every reaction to be a revelation.¬†

When you start to understand what these annoyances are trying to _teach_ you, you can start to accept yourself ‚Äì and others ‚Äì with more grace.¬†

## [Wisdom from On Purpose](https://www.jayshetty.me/podcast)

Why are so many men feeling lonely today? And how do we begin to rebuild real connection? 

In this week‚Äôs [episode](https://www.jayshetty.me/podcast), Radhi and I explore a growing truth that many are struggling to name: men are craving deeper friendships but often don‚Äôt know where to turn. We talk about why so many male friendships stay on the surface, how emotional expression is still seen as weakness, and what it really takes to create bonds that feel safe, honest, and nourishing. We share personal stories about the work it takes to maintain friendships, the courage required to be vulnerable, and how one meaningful conversation can shift everything. If you or someone you care about has ever felt alone in a crowded room, this one‚Äôs for you.

Wherever you‚Äôre listening from, I hope you hear something that stays with you. The [full episode](https://www.jayshetty.me/podcast) is available now.

# Today‚Äôs Wiser Choice

When someone pushes your buttons, take a breath. Instead of reacting, get curious.  What‚Äôs it trying to show you?

**Try this: **Write down what bothered you. Maybe your friend ignored your idea and pushed her own instead. Or maybe a coworker took credit for something you did. 

Then, go a little deeper. Why did it bother you? Saying ‚Äúbecause it‚Äôs annoying‚Äù doesn‚Äôt quite get to the root. We‚Äôre looking for what‚Äôs underneath ‚Äì the value or feeling that was touched. 

You can use these sentence starters to guide you: 

* ‚ÄúThis bothered me because I value‚Ä¶‚Äù 

* ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt like this behavior because it makes me feel‚Ä¶‚Äù 

* ‚ÄúIf I did this to someone else, I would‚Ä¶‚Äù

column7: Why you DON‚ÄôT need experience to coach
column9:
Hey Candace,

¬†

The people who make the best coaches‚Ä¶

¬†

‚Ä¶often start out struggling with doubts that they‚Äôre ready.

¬†

‚ùå It‚Äôs not time.

¬†

‚ùå It‚Äôs rarely money.

‚ùå And it‚Äôs almost never experience.

¬†

It‚Äôs belief.

¬†

Belief that they‚Äôre not good enough.

¬†

That other people have a magic ‚Äúsomething‚Äù they don‚Äôt.

¬†

I‚Äôve worked with successful CEOs and people at the top of their industry.

And the truth is, they all had doubts like these too.

¬†

But here‚Äôs why they succeeded:

¬†

‚úÖ They started before they felt ready.

‚úÖ They practiced, and the skills came.

‚úÖ They let themselves be guided and kept learning.

That‚Äôs exactly why I created the Jay Shetty Certification School.

To give aspiring coaches like you the space, support, and structure to grow into your new role as a coach.

¬†

With tools you can use to confidently create real, life change - for yourself and others.

¬†

And if you start now ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/enroll-2025/?el=price-email-experience-164-2&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+164-2&utm_content_name=Why+you+DON%E2%80%99T+need+experience+to+coach&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io ), you‚Äôll not only be transforming lives‚Ä¶

You‚Äôll also be saving money - joining before enrollment fees increase on May 1st.

¬†

That means you get the complete, upgraded 2025 program (at 2024 rates).

¬†

You don‚Äôt have to come with any answers.

¬†

Just an open mind to start learning.

¬†

Click here to enroll now ‚Üí ( https://pages.jayshettycoaching.com/enroll-2025/?el=price-email-experience-164-2&utm_campaign_name=JSCS%3A+Prospects+Week+164-2&utm_content_name=Why+you+DON%E2%80%99T+need+experience+to+coach&utm_medium_name=email_action&utm_source_name=customer.io )

I‚Äôll help you grow into the coach you dream of becoming. column9:
---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: CUNY, School of Professional Studies <admissions@sps.cuny.edu>
Date: Tue, May 6, 2025 at 8:11‚ÄØPM
Subject: How to Set Up Your Student Account at CUNY SPS
To: <aicoaching2025@gmail.com>



Dear Candace,

To register for classes at CUNY SPS, you will need to set up your student
account in *CUNYfirst*
<https://mx.technolutions.net/ss/c/u001.IxUnrKQmsIVM0i3eYI-DD5E9fmg0wd02A_iqpDNLjiQUJWNKw01Z-MGik-zGLBvM/4ga/TpFEgrnpQN2JCONqT5ejkw/h0/h001.6kcrDHM1g-DDtnz3G05NDzA_2UZe9ULeLiCVnRIUwnI>.
This is the system that you will use to register for classes, view your
class schedule and financial aid, and much more.

To access your account, please visit the CUNYfirst Log-In page at
https://home.cunyfirst.cuny.edu
<https://mx.technolutions.net/ss/c/u001.IxUnrKQmsIVM0i3eYI-DD5E9fmg0wd02A_iqpDNLjiQHOvBCDqO_aJduQKQec7Je/4ga/TpFEgrnpQN2JCONqT5ejkw/h1/h001.lSzX320btIXShDbTSqgkavOIa7LW3WrBPvtcqyYvg0A>
and follow the instructions below:

   - For First-time Users: Activate Your Account
   <https://mx.technolutions.net/ss/c/u001.jxaZRujEt1lhE0WEp4QewNALO7g8W4-NkEZcMj3BRrZjr16Y-MbIbK6k37fhUym5FDrW02FkQhUFbWDjWui3Y4SxC6Hbvw2RYQjIehwGjge6pZvPgojQAFxlbhHOgsLckf8yGeZlJarfkN2ZCTnfcw/4ga/TpFEgrnpQN2JCONqT5ejkw/h2/h001.4NnlMX_6dAFcy8U0qJt0qgycssSUtfJ0nBzP32cqnIs>
   - For Returning Users: Forgot Your Password?
   <https://mx.technolutions.net/ss/c/u001.jxaZRujEt1lhE0WEp4QewNALO7g8W4-NkEZcMj3BRrZjr16Y-MbIbK6k37fhUym5FDrW02FkQhUFbWDjWui3Y4SxC6Hbvw2RYQjIehwGjge6pZvPgojQAFxlbhHOgsLckf8yGeZlJarfkN2ZCTnfcw/4ga/TpFEgrnpQN2JCONqT5ejkw/h3/h001.pZjh1gPAE9wsWDr-bXfKAx3SHDb62gUsY6P5PqlsNek>

Please note if you were assigned an identification number by the Admissions
office because you did not have a social security number at the time of
application, you will need to use this number in lieu of a social security
number while setting up your CUNYfirst account. Please contact Office of
Admissions at admissions@sps.cuny.edu if you need your identification
number again.

Once you activate your CUNYfirst account, you will be able to register for
classes during the registration period. For detailed instructions on how to
register, please visit the Student Self Service

column7: Why I Stopped Calling Myself a ‚ÄúYouTuber‚Äù
column9:
Hey friends,

I recently had a conversation with Paul Millerd, who, if you
didn‚Äôt know, has become somewhat famous on the internet for
encouraging people to quit their jobs (which sounds more dramatic
than it actually is üòÖ). He‚Äôs written two books - The Pathless
Path (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/92u972n8rdtnh6z9v66i9hzpxl933iwhz0g26/08hwhgu22548vqsp/aHR0cHM6Ly9nZW5pLnVzL2hwU1JwTkQ=
) and Good Work (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/92u972n8rdtnh6z9v66i9hzpxl933iwhz0g26/8ghqh3uoov84zwal/aHR0cHM6Ly9nZW5pLnVzL3dNeHdr
) - and I‚Äôve been a huge fan of his writing for years.

Back in 2019/2020 when I was grappling with big questions like
‚Äúwhat even is work?‚Äù and ‚Äúwhat am I supposed to be doing with my
life?‚Äù, discovering Paul‚Äôs newsletter and eventually his book
gave me permission to explore a different path. I‚Äôd been skirting
around the edges of this creator / entrepreneur life, but
something about his writing made it feel okay to actually try it.

Anyway, we recorded a conversation recently (which we‚Äôll be
turning into a long-form video for the main channel, so look out
for that), and we talked about this idea of labels.

Now, from a productivity perspective, we often celebrate labels.

The whole ‚Äúidentity-based goals‚Äù thing - so calling yourself ‚Äúa
runner‚Äù rather than just ‚Äúsomeone who runs‚Äù for example - is
supposed to help us achieve our goals, and it definitely works.

Labelling myself as a ‚ÄúYouTuber‚Äù helped me take YouTube more
seriously in the early days, and adding the word ‚Äúwriter‚Äù to my
Instagram bio helped me actually finish Feel-Good Productivity (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/92u972n8rdtnh6z9v66i9hzpxl933iwhz0g26/vqh3hmuoo765llbw/aHR0cHM6Ly9nZW5pLnVzL2xpZmVub3Rlc19wYXBlcmJhY2s=
) - leaning into these identities was genuinely useful at first.

But there‚Äôs a hidden cost that I‚Äôve only recently started to
notice.

When you adopt any sort of label like ‚Äúauthor‚Äù or ‚ÄúYouTuber‚Äù or
whatever the thing may be, you unconsciously start following a
script of what that label should do - even when those activities
have stopped being enjoyable. And eventually, you might feel
trapped by this identity.

So there‚Äôs something I‚Äôve been doing recently where I‚Äôve started
internally dropping the label of ‚ÄúYouTuber.‚Äù

I know that sounds odd given that I have over 6 million
subscribers and make YouTube videos for a living. But when I
labelled myself as a ‚ÄúYouTuber‚Äù there was always this
subconscious script running in the back of my mind being like
‚Äúwhat‚Äôs the next video?‚Äù and ‚Äúshould I check the analytics?‚Äù and
stuff like that, because that‚Äôs just what "YouTubers" do.

So I‚Äôve decided to confine all my YouTube stuff to Tuesdays in
the week - this is when I think about videos, scripts, and
filming. And then for the rest of the week, I‚Äôve got time slots
to work on the various apps we‚Äôre building, write my email
newsletters, and create new courses like the Lifestyle Business
Academy, which feels really fun and exciting at the moment.

I‚Äôm sure it won‚Äôt stay that way forever - everything, at least
for me, has a period of excitement and then eventually tapers
off. But by that point, I‚Äôll probably be interested in something
else, whether that be homeschooling or gardening, who knows.

The point is, I‚Äôve found it incredibly liberating to drop any
labels and just focus on the bundle of activities I enjoy right
now.

So instead of ‚ÄúI‚Äôm a YouTuber‚Äù (with all the pressure and
expectations it comes with), it‚Äôs more like ‚ÄúI currently enjoy
making videos on Tuesdays, building apps, writing, and teaching
courses, but some of those things might change next year.‚Äù

Because the goal isn‚Äôt to arrive somewhere and become something
fixed and definite - the goal is just to keep moving in the
direction of things we enjoy.

I certainly don‚Äôt have all this figured out, but since making
this shift, I‚Äôve actually felt more productive and energised, not
less. And this whole process of figuring out your actual values
and direction, rather than locking yourself into some rigid
identity, is something we dive deep into within the Life Compass
module of LifeOS (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/92u972n8rdtnh6z9v66i9hzpxl933iwhz0g26/l2heh6ull9pge2hg/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPWxhYmVsXzIwJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1wcm9kdWN0aXZlbm90ZXM=
).

There‚Äôs a whole bunch of prompts to help you figure out what
actually matters to you - like imagining your own eulogy (sounds
morbid, I know, but it‚Äôs surprisingly clarifying), or exploring
what you‚Äôd do if money weren‚Äôt a concern - so if that sounds
interesting, you can check it out here (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/92u972n8rdtnh6z9v66i9hzpxl933iwhz0g26/l2heh6ull9pge2hg/aHR0cHM6Ly9hbGlhYmRhYWwuY29tL2xpZmVvcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPWxhYmVsXzIwJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1wcm9kdWN0aXZlbm90ZXM=
).

And if you feel like the labels you carry are weighing you down
at the moment, ask yourself: what would it feel like to hold them
a bit more lightly? And what bundle of activities do I enjoy
doing right now?

Hit reply and let me know - I‚Äôd genuinely love to hear your
thoughts on this.

Have a great rest of your week üòä

Ali xx

Dear friends,

Last week, China barred its major tech companies from buying Nvidia chips. This move received only modest attention in the media, but has implications far beyond what‚Äôs widely appreciated. Specifically, it signals that China has progressed sufficiently in semiconductors to break away from dependence on advanced chips designed in the U.S., the vast majority of which are manufactured in Taiwan. It also highlights the U.S. vulnerability to possible disruptions in Taiwan at a moment when China is becoming less vulnerable.

After the U.S. started restricting AI chip sales to China, China dramatically ramped up its semiconductor research and investment to move toward self-sufficiency. These efforts are starting to bear fruit, and China‚Äôs willingness to cut off Nvidia is a strong sign of its faith in its domestic capabilities. For example, the new DeepSeek-R1-Safe model was trained on 1000 Huawei Ascend chips. While individual Ascend chips are significantly less powerful than individual Nvidia or AMD chips, Huawei‚Äôs system-level design approach to orchestrating how a much larger number of chips work together seems to be paying off. For example, Huawei‚Äôs CloudMatrix 384 system of 384 chips aims to compete with Nvidia‚Äôs GB200, which uses 72 higher-capability chips.

Today, U.S. access to advanced semiconductors is heavily dependent on Taiwan‚Äôs TSMC, which manufactures the vast majority of the most advanced chips. Unfortunately, U.S. efforts to ramp up domestic semiconductor manufacturing have been slow. I am encouraged that one fab at the TSMC Arizona facility is now operating, but issues of workforce training, culture, licensing and permitting, and the supply chain are still being addressed, and there is still a long road ahead for the U.S. facility to be a viable substitute for manufacturing in Taiwan.

If China gains independence from Taiwan manufacturing significantly faster than the U.S., this would leave the U.S. much more vulnerable to possible disruptions in Taiwan, whether through natural disasters or man-made events. If manufacturing in Taiwan is disrupted for any reason and Chinese companies end up accounting for a large fraction of global semiconductor manufacturing capabilities, that would also help China gain tremendous geopolitical influence.

Despite occasional moments of heightened tensions and large-scale military exercises, Taiwan has been mostly peaceful since the 1960s. This peace has helped the people of Taiwan to prosper and allowed AI to make tremendous advances, built on top of chips made by TSMC. I hope we will find a path to maintaining peace for many decades more.

But hope is not a plan. In addition to working to ensure peace, practical work lies ahead to multi-source, build more chip fabs in more nations, and enhance the resilience of the semiconductor supply chain. Dependence on any single manufacturer invites shortages, price spikes, and stalled innovation the moment something goes sideways.

Keep building,

Andrew

Agents of Commerce

Google launched an open protocol for agentic payments that enables agents based on any large language model to purchase items over the internet.

What‚Äôs new: Agent Payments Protocol (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LRP3prCCW95jsWP6lZ3kFW3BvWPp3kbJG-W2KDSRB47VM3nW4vdF3H8s94dpW1-FKQz1ZcTmSW1S3vrv5f1CyvW8jXlyp803SdKW4L7LyN2x2FLzW4Kr8Zh1cXWxQW63389w2DHs4NW78dmVD3Z_nd0N3Y5x707Wg3_Vjzv4j8gpKTHW5yM5_M4PM612W8fqq614QRQP6W2_09Dk6xHgfMW2C5mbX8dZtljW8rzwfc3wKCLDW1232_92lBdk2W7MvYsS7z-QBLW12jVV757gRglW2M4P_41DdJgDW4JW45g4BsvWmW3Kr2ss7txqTGW4Z3NSY6yM3yzW6FLYLB2dd5rhW62xcwG1vjtkbVk0xcH3d52NSW37fBV43HXJBbW6w78BB22Wp2TW3Pvlms6VC_1Mf8G1C1204 ) (AP2) is designed for buyers and sellers to securely initiate, authorize, and close purchases. AP2 works with Google‚Äôs A2A and Anthropic‚Äôs similar MCP, open protocols that instruct agents or provide access to data and APIs. It manages diverse payment types including credit cards, bank transfers, digital payments, and cryptocurrency.

How it works: Agentic payments pose challenges to security, such as manipulation by malicious actors, and liability, particularly with respect to whether a user or agent is to blame for mistakes. AP2 aims to solve these problems by using cryptographically signed contracts called mandates. Three distinct mandates record the terms of the purchase, its fulfillment, and the user‚Äôs authorization of payment. If a fraudulent or incorrect transaction occurs, the payment processor can consult this record to see which party is accountable. To buy an item using AP2:

- An intent mandate specifies rules for the purchase such as price limits, timing, and the item‚Äôs attributes. It may create an intent mandate while a user is present or ahead of time. For instance, if a buyer instructs an agent to ‚Äúbuy [brand and model] running shoes the moment they go on sale,‚Äù the agent will prompt the user to specify and authorize the terms of the mandate, such as the desired top price, size, and color.
- A cart mandate covers the other end of the sale. This contract describes the contents of the virtual shopping cart including a description of items sold, their prices, and terms of the deal.
- A payment mandate tells a payment network (a financial institution plus payment processor that moves funds electronically) that the transaction was authorized by a user or an agent, so it can complete the transaction.

Behind the news: Many companies have experimented with agentic payments with varying degrees of success. For example, last year Stripe launched (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LPK5m_5PW50kH_H6lZ3mFW5pZcTt6YwmsVN4FmGXkyV17MW3VXf0W6prqNjN1BqCNc9GZZCW4K1dB97FQnmsW4l54HT69_HpTW4nRQsL4QBGMmN9kTTdRx0rR4N1XqS0bxCtQXW94P9mH4mkVL1W7Spkf08cG-m8W8zySy42ZjgbmW1P76fF2ggWnhVymY3-459MJBW2pl1gp93kHp-W1tXD9j7Pds9LW6Gc1811X0WBZW2mfJn13TVrG0W1HWTh53yvYWbW41JNt38j48Y8W74zZyH5cGRtwV3FP-q5Q-QQsW1Fwcjl7ZXbkNW8bM53k7xdy94W5kttKF3Hb1RmW3shdbQ3gQKQ4N7PSx2rcl48ZW5s0w36132XQwW7YRL3Y7zSxFgW8WNFnH93VhdQW6tybbF7sq-mWW5tJM086X7lq_f6LTspY04 ) an agentic payment toolkit that issues a one-time debit card for each purchase. This approach reduces risk, but it requires Stripe‚Äôs payment system, particular models, and specific agentic frameworks. Google‚Äôs approach is more comprehensive, initially including more than 60 partners including payment processors, financial institutions, and software giants.

Why it matters: AP2 opens up automated sales in which any participant can buy and sell, and it does this in a standardized, flexible way. For instance, a user could tell an agent to book a vacation in a specific location with a specific budget. The agent could transmit those requirements to many sellers‚Äô agents that might assemble customized packages to meet the user‚Äôs demands. Then the user‚Äôs agent could either present the packages to the user or choose one itself. The buyer would get the vacation they want and the seller would make a valuable sale, while AI did the haggling.

We‚Äôre thinking: The internet didn‚Äôt make travel agents obsolete, it made them agentic!

What ChatGPT Users Want

What do ChatGPT‚Äôs 700 million weekly active users do with it? OpenAI teamed up with a Harvard economist to find out.

What‚Äôs new: ChatGPT users are turning to the chatbot increasingly for personal matters rather than work, and the gender balance of the user base is shifting, OpenAI found (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LQW3prCCW7lCdLW6lZ3nwW70LMdq3Lq-vvW2-cq5-8s64TBW6Phrn66vBFRCW8HbS_n3kyVSqW4bFNh89kjw6CW6kHJ_b6nMWgVW33ZrR27KtD12W1BH-z-8F0Zw_V2tD9w3zYFzzW5-JqQf2TFlHdV6GNnt252t5QW7T6TmV7gHP-vW3HyNXS1N1ZsGW3nkFkn8r0s-SW8MlJNm7y9NkWW7LWX367kMB46W37FwWJ7TDKLHVVXHHl9fSJmrW2CqTrS7yPF54W7XClCQ3Cs_dtVY_pT499BY2vW7W19858wMrLhW62RsMx2h7sjKW12Z6c33_YChcf2Dvwhb04 ) in a large-scale study. ‚ÄúHow People Use ChatGPT,‚Äù a preliminary report published by the National Bureau of Economic Research, is available (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LQC3prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3mcW1WRbRK8X-JfmW1p294g5zfbjrN5THkQ2vmJD5W3mDhcT58gJ2DF43Sbj7xblPN7RPm7Y61V_RW8dn55c4MKDH2W7bZldT7DD7RBW6M75L687B-qQW99LFVG2FKtbFW8kbfQ73fbDr-N82WYcfb06GwW2JSzd93wj6YJM4K6RWqr3SGVsvHDz1swtWkW2fPLh07_FSDhW5v91QN7l9FnLW8mn3jb5cZPwKW6g95WC88gLD7W5YTN247G7r7XW25qKZk6bjGRYW6wJv4Q6jtFc6f1VxF3K04 )  in return for an institutional email address.

How it works: The study examined 1.58 million messages entered by users and drawn at random from over 1.1 million conversations between May 2024 and July 2025.

- The messages were written by logged-in users over 18 who used consumer-level (as opposed to business) subscriptions.
- The authors classified users by gender (based on names the authors deemed typically masculine, feminine, or indeterminate), self-reported age, and geography.
- They classified messages by topic, general intention (such as asking for information or requesting action), and specific task (such as writing or coding).

Results: Most users of ChatGPT were young adults, and apparently more women are joining their ranks. Uses shifted from work to more personal tasks over the course of the study period. Writing and guidance were most popular uses, followed closely by seeking information.

- ChatGPT was most popular with users between 18 and 25 years old, who sent 46 percent of the messages. Users between 26 and 66 were more likely to use ChatGPT for work.
- Women may now outnumber men using ChatGPT. Messages from users with names classified as typically feminine increased from 37 percent in January 2024 to 52 percent by June 2025.
- Messages categorized as asking were more common than messages categorized as doing (requests for generated output such as plans, writing, or code) or expressing (such as idle conversation, reflection, or playing a role). The most common requests were for practical guidance (28.3 percent) or writing (28.1 percent), while seeking information was nearly as popular (21.3 percent).
- Uses of ChatGPT for personal matters rose. In June 2024, messages divided roughly equally between work and non-work uses. By July 2025, roughly 73 percent of them likely were not related to work. (Overall use grew during that time. The number of likely non-work messages increased by around 8 times, while the number of work-related messages increased by more than 3 times.)
- Among non-work uses, the most common were seeking information (24.4 percent) or practical guidance (28.8 percent). When ChatGPT was used for work, the most common use was writing, mostly requests to edit, critique, translate, or otherwise transform existing text rather than produce all-new text.

Behind the news: OpenAI said its report is the largest study of chatbot usage undertaken to date, but its peers have published similar research. Anthropic released its third Economic Index (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LRb3prCCW7Y8-PT6lZ3lBW2Ng5g15bVRBCW4QDnSP9kyJPgW116Vg28njJfMW60-DGW1Kw-kCW6MSKfJ3xwqzcN4FwMdjxKv87MbfqcWTwd7bW2rpVB61f-tC1W3j48Vt47yYkGW7_0bcS6D8bxHW7787Xd3WRw4CW2hf1d926ls7yV6tqw_60kyYpW5h1vY94v9dwBW5DLjwr7b7PC2Vj_b7r7Fz8mRW9h0vrX39HFMVW3ksDSq4HJ2_NW5_6lBB1v8W4ZW2C0yhY2Lb6xyW6_0m6D6MsfWDW6dGwvt8qcXZKW2w3lpV11830DW122NgX1SLrM5N977Lpqpymx4W7y24t23Mmd-8f42FP8s04 ) , which analyzes consumer and business use of its Claude models. Anthropic‚Äôs study shows that Claude API users are much more likely to automate tasks than consumer users. Claude is used overwhelmingly for computational and mathematical tasks, but education, arts and media, and office and administrative support are steadily rising.

Why it matters: In OpenAI‚Äôs study (and Anthropic‚Äôs), AI users and uses are becoming more diverse. The initial user of AI chatbots was disproportionately likely to be based in the U.S., highly educated, highly paid, male, young, and focused on technology. Nearly 3 years after ChatGPT‚Äôs introduction, they are far more varied, as are their wants, needs, and expectations.

We‚Äôre thinking: Early on, it seemed as though large language models would be most useful for work. But people are using them to seek information and advice about personal matters, plan their lives, and express themselves. It turns out that we need more intelligence in our whole lives, not just at the office.

Sports Betting Goes Agentic

AI agents are getting in on the action of online sports gambling.

What‚Äôs new: Several startups cater to betting customers by offering AI-powered sports analysis, chat, and tips, Wired reported (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LRv3prCCW8wLKSR6lZ3m_W88N49h1YX-y7W1yXXDq32QQ3rW63PJz07wBxqSW2CzDWH5ZYJhzN3MsWSwkPbFZVFWh7V7R7dQrW6-qSDV1XmvgcW1xp9y25744TpW3ktc_d5BzT_sN1-kb8S2-VzXVbWr7q9cdyMRW1qZ_lk5TDkrGW1d-PQD5X8BYHW7Wm-v36Bc92QW245MbP7QDZKpW8wZ7Kn7jy6gLW2dWThb1D9PrzW9kynpl93NDvgW3n9CTw3C-nPRW7-yyLJ4rVZr0W1VdYY23_n6C-W3C1Xq-25RDtHW4FntGr95qN81W1pxzSB2NSDHWW4cGjZZ7VfskwW8T929q1N3p0JW22zSgM30gXPhW7m-Q6Z8htR7tdJX7FW04 ) . Some established gambling operations are adding AI capabilities to match.

How it works: Most AI sports-betting startups analyze which bets are the most statistically likely to pay off based on publicly available data. Increasingly, agents suggest specific bets. Only a few take bets from users and pay winnings to them, and fewer offer agents that actively place bets on third-party web sites on a user‚Äôs behalf.

- Monster.bet (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LQj3prCCW69sMD-6lZ3mnVK_DNZ1Cq0qSW5j_7mZ54pvY1W2snXLG3QD7S6VKl86b6kS3V2W4BQmwq8dvwq2W7WhbmG8brHHcN1fV3Z4BFWppW606CrQ7k1PGQW2-yDjg1t-FKCVx9XhS4m-YJdW11QYrs2rd4NcW22MHH92cp2dBW4rqfVp8w928TN125H2MVSMxSW5dMqnM85PX1FN4H6dCqXpRsvW6140h6325VyGW4pV9fM3P3NYhN7Rf1VxVJvyZW5BWNBW3cGmW4f24GYh604 ) hosts MonsterGPT, a GPT-style chatbot that uses retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) to gather sports data from across the web while a proprietary algorithm predicts winners. The chatbot allows bettors to ask questions, and a history function tracks the results of bets they place and tailors its analysis to their strategies. Access to Monster costs $77 a month.
- Rithmm, based in Massachusetts, allows users to create their own ‚Äúprediction models‚Äù using no-code tools. It also focuses on ‚Äúprop bets‚Äù (not whether a team will win a game, but whether a player will achieve a particular outcome like score a touchdown). Subscriptions start at $30 a month.
- With roots in fantasy sports, FanDuel is an older sports-betting operation that has integrated AI. Unlike many competitors, it takes bets and pays winnings. The mobile app integrates a chatbot called AceAI (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LRv3prCCW8wLKSR6lZ3mrW2BsynM9cR4D4W5vHcQx5wMhTWW5P57NV21Z91nW7slG7r59dYsdW4VFmLQ4VwtThN8WhmDHB3lyjW56PBdm7JDHRgW6rSGhW3X624BW95gyjF1sLqjGW4D5zFR2fK7YDW31ThxQ45RVZkV1dNjj73pKPjW4X3GST759s1-W1CzR555Jmpp3W52PV0P1X-_0xW6J7cBl3wYcL_W51cQrL28z90zW8lWYpP4-9CDgW7lkhmL7VMq5yN7XxHCPcJQn5W8yxCSF1w95QVW545YSP6_6X-FW2DvsBp6m4rNGN56f_ffm7qhSW2hSZST43YhNlVGwBR71J8bf0W4yKKPc3L6ZVxW2tdn3k4Xfywdf1n0fFC04 ) that helps users construct bets that require more than one event to occur; for example, that football champions Argentina will win a particular match and their star Lionel Messi will score at least one goal.
- Sire (formerly DraiftKing [sic]) uses an agentic approach. AI agents currently have limited access to bank accounts and other payment services like PayPal or Venmo, so Sire‚Äôs agents place bets using a crypto wallet. This enables an agent to react to events within a match and place bets automatically faster than a human can. For example, if a tennis player serves an ace, an automated bet can be made that the next serve will also be an ace. But instead of placing separate bets by individual bettors, Sire sells shares to customers who divide any profits from a wide range of bets.
- Few other betting agents have succeeded. The blockchain platform Zilliqa developed an agent called Ava for picking horse-race winners but abandoned it because synchronizing the agent, crypto wallets, and betting sites ‚Äî all of which operate independently ‚Äî was too slow. Some other purportedly agentic tools, including one called WagerGPT, collapsed under inflated promises.

Behind the news: Most AI gambling startups are based in the United States, where online betting recently became legal. In 2024, Americans bet over $150 billion (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LPK5m_5PW50kH_H6lZ3lFW94Wh8d6htSdQN2QMd_6vqMYmW6wJrtM51Ygb_N4mRh77cKNBqW6Dqj_Y3QGp2JW1cF8P19bcNfdW4fcPWv7dTklGW8wQj5s39210fW7KgLl769GZxdW18rtcx3cFT2qW7rfNw-4_2LBsN7KRclPVbM0SW17hzpD5lf8N6W4D8WRz11wyHMW4yK6j98jxBNpW5VhqMq1Y_9NTW5PRwXY6GMsY0W51y6fn6sbyp8W2mPvy73xpwQlW4kbKL-4j8W1LW297nJm72QcLFW1fYqgt52m5-RW2jZzGh2yJH7KW3DKpTZ2P-SsPW4FpjGc2chWBTW4Lxy5w2KkZp8W6Xlc9m3XBty4W25vDTY3dDMP3VTKj_g3fGf1_W8tNf5D4nLT7WW1CDTtH78P5wlW5644w_6_QfTpf7SgzSb04 ) on legal sports wagers, up 22 percent from 2023. The share of online betting has grown steadily from 25 percent of the total in 2024 to 30 percent in 2025 and shows no sign of slowing down.

Why it matters: Online gambling is an AI laboratory that uses nearly every emerging element of the technology. It requires quantitative reasoning to analyze bets, RAG to scour sports statistics and other relevant information, classification models to identify potentially profitable bets, and payment agents to place bets automatically. As these technologies advance, betting analysis and tools will advance with them.

We‚Äôre thinking: Whether you gamble with cash or just wager your time and energy, learning more about AI is a smart bet.

Faster Reinforcement Learning

Fine-tuning large language models via reinforcement learning is computationally expensive, but researchers found a way to streamline the process.

What‚Äôs new: Qinsi Wang and colleagues at UC Berkeley and Duke University developed GAIN-RL (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LQC3prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3pzW6YzKMd1hK8wWW3y5qzQ7S0xNxW833ChF3LHgcZW45ZZ6k644nP-W7RTn2n6mBDRrMT07m_NHjt3N5h3prC3tbN_W2pR6pY5J62H9W2MSxVT2Xd8FqW29mN8W6tySQgW570bx032HbFyW8nJ70-9g4mH2W2ftZfP8P_yP5W6Vzv4j6VkjqmW37vK0j17NwwWN5X95Wm4n2PTW30zydB18p1hFMBwFWZJ82mkV2Q2yt3gQwFBW9kD1QN868xPCW5cjyZT361MFrVPdRXn7bLqF9f21qmBP04 ) , a method that accelerates reinforcement learning fine-tuning by selecting training examples automatically based on the model‚Äôs own internal signals, specifically the angles between vector representations of tokens. The code is available (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LQC3prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3n6W4stXzJ9fsw8bW4K4gqh5bg6ZtW5jgkNc6nChQVW1qWvQV2G_SLsW87DZm65JnjB8VrbxZt3x9zjVW4PRrkc6FnhmSW3hS8NC59h0vPW67rcH98hpznDW65HlPL3DFSFGW2gZcVP5PkxTdVXKm_B10ZwYfW50pKmw83rswCW5LQW0x2gL5RXW3mfqV32xhPynW2mvGbr6c7_JLN73HM452QKMYN5l7j9f1Zs0PW4lJr4b8yncVtW3kt8TN2WVQg9W8T3Wb66qF_vrW5QWwgK5ks1JVf1ttqsj04 )  on GitHub.

Key insight: The cosine similarity between a model‚Äôs vector representations of input tokens governs the magnitude of gradient updates during training. Specifically, the sum of those similarities that enter a model‚Äôs classification layer, called the angle concentration, governs the magnitude of gradient updates. Examples with higher angle concentration produce larger gradient updates. The magnitude of a gradient update in turn determines the effectiveness of a given training example: The larger the update, the more the model learns. Prioritizing the most-effective examples before transitioning to less-effective ones enhances training efficiency while adding little preprocessing overhead.

How it works: The authors separately fine-tuned Qwen 2.5 1.5B, Qwen 2.5 7B, and Llama 3.2 3B using the GRPO (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LQC3prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3kBW5Q6TyR1lqzYPW3ZgS5w83ckjhW2dP4-B4w-_9JN7xRvFvWx08kVdYK9l6fxLKLW69lpb82c_VMrW6-Xr4P2bSpqSW8VPf1K7bt_bHW3WH20V5wJltlN8n9JKRNgHt6W2bygMZ3B3wtHW5GsFZz8q7z0DVmJh_j77N17GV9-hqF3JqLW_N8kN7CkFDLrjW3LhVYc8H_txyW64SHBR4hMmpHW7jWLsn4s_KpjW3496zv5lpCKgW6YhkpS79CTF3W79vyqk8hPLh1W4Zs5pq3z7VTcf25V3_T04 ) reinforcement learning algorithm with examples ordered according to their angle concentration. The datasets included math problems in GSM8K (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LQC3prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3mvW2HJCkZ5_02w4W2lFmwf7qKgzMW1rYk1q4RcN6cW5NRX6G8Nyx1yW10Cc6G7g8_88W4jl0Fr2ZrWJxW6d69C63DNsnRW6ZmhTm5mhPr0W3cn8SB67ZJdBW3J8JQL7KNCKZW1nLkWW2lfSzXW2WkxfK2g3v1tW4N9wd-732Hb_W10GP1v8wJhgRN8WdQfWptnMdW8h3MF233FjyKW8Bq4yp8bHQ59W7_RFXr5ZTpQ-W1kVYw01D8L3yN1TRdLTZmXm3W2CLhgy6LY0lgW3NQSTX3VTwlzf3HwMpb04 ) and AMC 23 (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LQW3prCCW7lCdLW6lZ3pZW6DWYdw469fxSW3HN8TP36Y9qXW7q0P7x6KLyM6N24z283kzM_WN7Rm6yFzCdHLW3tLt5q7fNZYKW2LLyrq2dkyr-W1MdYlp8gBVX-W8G02jz17C1CxW7yY2c66-fC-yW85T8vP2fp5wKN15bMm_fPwNDW33vDNG6vsq9rW140pBK7wQjC_Vv1nzF58SnfMW4LrhYP8W2h6tW1ySM2N5LcWzmW14VhGc6XvCKDW3dJRhq7NfqZzVt2r0m6RHvPmW5Cs5Y381kV5ZW1r4yj92PS3ZSVq-dgG8Z8cvcW1xFDc57nYMVCf4_4stP04 ) , and coding problems in LiveCodeBench (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LQC3prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3lsW6x8Z-K2lhHr5W4pYw0z3Sr4Q1W98v03m5DZx9rV-pPmf7FdM92W2WGzDB1ZjwwWN88F75fNZFsWW1GXcHh73CRM9W1pgFNN8-dhNrVD-S0Q2jgYQ6W30m8dQ4x9XfkW5K-7m07VMCvTVFwhSv5YXkDHMVWrjd-nVZ8VWzCp072N8NXN7hmHBwqgM8QN3TYjbbn5QMJW2nfGqX96891pW8sh71B28kT8DW5vbmFL8CMy2yW12SvzY8ggKgSW18LFMC6GJRCkVMvzJm5ZVcc7f1xZ-3K04 ) and HumanEval+ (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LQC3prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3ppW1QPq-p2KY_C4W1xcBXL2ZCPVwW5XxS8z3pZZfVW6Swm_m4yJX5rW5hnhQR7w3cJlW5fS0qq8HbX3HW7H-Nvd3QPgdkW3Z9H3j3Z_gB5W7_ftt-2q0z0fW2_gdsN7k6WgdW3Yc3d81MPzZfW5qf9H54KQCkCW4M0Cmp3V6TZkVgVLzH1Cq-5GN26PzpFdpCXkN6Smpcv318xDW5ZXyg44VPMK2W4lnqP53TwXmwW43VrjL6_C4rSW5m-1K68bYcddW1c1f2D8p_CK5W6C2ldd3nlNBXdBkHj804 ) .

- Given a training set, the authors calculated the angle concentration of each example by performing a single forward pass on the entire dataset. They sorted examples from highest to lowest angle concentration.
- They fine-tuned the models, focusing first on examples with the highest angle concentrations and shifting toward lower angle concentrations as training progressed. They tracked the models‚Äô learning according to accuracy and the angle concentration on each batch of data. They shifted the focus more toward less-effective examples as the model learned and shifted less when it struggled.
- They continued training for 200 epochs.

Results: The authors compared models that were fine-tuned using GAIN-RL with counterparts that used GRPO performed on randomly ordered examples. GAIN-RL generally accelerated learning by a factor of 2.5.

- Whether the task involved math or coding, GAIN-RL took 70 to 80 training epochs to match the performance of fine-tuning using typical GRPO for 200 epochs.
- For instance, on GSM8K, Qwen 2.5 Math Instruct 7B after GAIN-RL fine-tuning achieved 92.0 percent accuracy after 70 epochs. The version fine-tuned on typical GRPO needed 200 epochs to reach the same performance.

Why it matters: Many strategies for ordering training examples rely on external, often expensive heuristics based on their difficulty, for example judgments by human annotators or a proprietary LLM. By using a simple signal generated by the model itself, this method provides a direct and efficient way to identify the most effective examples, making reinforcement learning much faster.

We‚Äôre thinking: Ordering training examples is much older than applying reinforcement learning to fine-tuning large language models. Applying earlier methods to more recent approaches holds many advances in machine learning!

Work With Andrew Ng

Join the teams that are bringing AI to the world! Check out job openings at DeepLearning.AI (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LQC3prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3q3TY6Fg68hft0W6DfDns2HwGK3W74JwtY3pGpjWN1RX7gZ_74hNW309fdL5SzRKRW2wXm4g6gWbsxW7-LvnC4jDZzlW6S9hWL6mWk4tW5gB0gg6k0lrJW5bTFKZ1nXkpTW5KLJp839S0f2W6RXGDb6Q73tbN7HZd0w6CpMbW9kJ3Gm1sBZYyW8KYqx12XLLymW5Y8dcy5XMJ7yN4WqcfFxKbMkV_lYQM2dXK3CW1FG_1M7Qxrx6VqZZ2z2XlbfBW7lkfS_4wp4TgN1R03Pb_3vK7f1xpDK004 ) , AI Fund (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LQC3prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3m_VK-rP488rz_dW9cPKQh8SLCWNW1GnbWY5V69hGW8LxJv24pdMGsW3-Tg3N38lsS4W1P2Wcm3WscDJV_vtMq1MCkn9W9f3qZ48x4R7pW1YcCcl7Gn8DQW4-_HF67nJ3s8W4G_nCw7HV8nNW4V5fqy6XBRKyW722rn72bvslkVX9mWT4RjPZ_W3N8n2R1xQ2rxVmXZbH42fHdzW2tRznR3MZkd0W5W1N7J92SXP-W462Vkx4V62HzW7Md2Lw7p3zPNN1HMcj7_fz43W2cWJ6_2qtYClf2BYk-404 ) , and Landing AI (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LQC3prCCW6N1vHY6lZ3nnW5D_hlw8wyz89W69Rbfj7w9pBqW6z38gn6J-g4SW1QjNqc19FV63W77vQKM90S67NW8W8c3_6D02C8W8bC14b3xgQBQW1XC6d71GcBZYW8kj5ZH2M6hDVW4w2FL78Mr4PLW3F4KtL2SnmNZW6dBDSv2nLKNQW8PFd435cMqX6W18fgG872_22yW9b1r4-8lm6YsW7QYdt39fJDJSW7qK0vm9kn_wPW2cfRxS22wvRYW8LzfLz2kZH5tW9g_Ptn4h2Fd4W8jQfPw1vfBl3VbN7_z1hvtD_f7q5qZT04 ) .

Subscribe and view previous issues here (https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VVDt-91cDYk7W7yRg808Nyh-lW5d86_w5CSHpXN5n2LQC3l5QzW6N1vHY6lZ3p2VLD8518Yqw8BW6fLSLM85mr2FW25Hjxy1x3bzpN7Lz7ZvCq_-RW5yRr7y2SjcKHW4dqZ3q41QDXZW7pQmWT5k5-pNN2LmWyx8WnT5W4TXvZ694kJBHW8-8ZBd4q_HVLW5QQXtk66nzcRW5_dFDZ59y2xyN4KdnGWMc51hVjxJSc6D7tCKW6JGx7R2hjNMwW7f5-FH5P4TD7W2_h3zF88m1SyW5p9VNG7lYzkXW3Xzgs52JdctVW7KJ1MD4ftKmsW3Dk74m8FZHhBN3kcdQ9qFsnqf7RKKFd04 ) .

column7: Thank you for applying to Oscar!
column9:
Hi Candace,

Thank you for your interest in Oscar. We appreciate you taking the time to complete your application for Data Scientist II: Risk Adjustment Analytics.

What happens next?

If your skills and experience align well with the requirements of the role, a member of our team will reach out to schedule a conversation with you.

Interested in learning more about Oscar? Click here ( https://www.themuse.com/profiles/oscarhealth ) to hear insights from our team.

Thank you once again,

Oscar Talent Acquisition
